Dennis "Denny" Correll (1946ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â‚¬ï¿½2002) was a one-time singer in the 1960s rock music group Blues Image as well as a Contemporary Christian musician active in the 1970s. He was an early touring member of the seminal Jesus music band Love Song, writing their tune "Changes" which appeared on that band's debut LP Love Song. He also was in the band Manna prior to his own solo Contemporary Christian music career.

Correll died from heart failure on 29 November 2002. He was 56.
